# Supabase in this codebase

Do **not** paste generic Supabase SSR snippets without checking how this app is actually wired. Patterns in official docs (middleware + `@supabase/ssr` only, `getAll`/`setAll` cookies) may not match the current tree.

## What to read before changing auth

- **`proxy.ts`** (root): Next.js 16 **Proxy** (replaces deprecated `middleware.ts`); session refresh and route guards. Uses `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs` (`createMiddlewareClient`). Export **`proxy`**, not `middleware`.
- **`src/lib/supabase/client.ts`**: Browser client — `@supabase/ssr` `createBrowserClient`.
- **`src/lib/supabase/server.ts`**: Server client — `@supabase/ssr` `createServerClient` with `get` / `set` / `remove` cookie helpers (legacy style; migration to `getAll`/`setAll` would be a deliberate refactor).
- **`src/app/page.tsx`**: Root `/` — must send **guests** to marketing (`/landing`) and **signed-in users** to their role default (see `getDefaultPathForRole` in `src/lib/auth/default-route.ts`). Never blindly client-redirect everyone to `/landing`.

## When adding features

- Prefer **`@supabase/ssr`** for new server/client helpers aligned with current Supabase docs.
- If you change cookie or session behavior, validate **`proxy.ts`**, **login**, and **`/auth/callback`** together so redirects and sessions stay consistent.
